1. Local init of the repository:

# Create a dir
$ mkdir test && cd test
$ git init
$ git status
$ ls -la

2. Check status of repository:
$ touch newfile && echo hello > newfile
$ git status	# new files should be untracked

3. Add files:
$ git add newfile
$ git status	# fiel is tracked and ready to be commited

4. Commit files:
$ git commit newfile -m "my first commit"	# we can use '-a' to commit all files of '.' to do it recursively
$ git status

5. Add and commit multiple files in one shot:
$ git add .	# only from current dir and subdirs recursively (not from repository root)
$ git status
$ git commit -m "my second commit" 
 

